rates","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/32.html",{"_":30,"ana":31,"ref":32},"base","#object.base","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/57.htm",{"_":34,"ana":35,"type":36,"subtype":37,"resp":38,"ref":39},"limestone","#material.inorganic.stone.sedimentary_rock.limestone.calcarenite","stone.calcarenite","unspecified","#Coccato","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/66.html",{"ana":41},"#condition.damaged",{"layout":43},{"p":44,"rs":45,"damage":49},"Line 1 is inscribed across the upper moulding (which is heavily damaged); the remainder of the text is engraved on the recessed front face, in two columns. The spacing between the columns after the first line is very irregular; column 2 has a half-line gap after line 2, meaning that the lines in the two columns are vertically out of synch after this point.",{"_":46,"ana":47,"ref":48},"chiselled","#execution.chiselled","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1",{"ana":50},"#text_condition.partly_illegible",{"lettering":52,"dimensions":53},"Neatly carved and regular letters, mostly without serifs, but some terminal wedges. Alpha with straight bar; epsilon on occasion has a slightly shorter mid-bar; zeta in form of I with wide horizontals; theta has short detached cross-bar; kappa has full-length arms; mu has vertical first and last, full length mid-strokes; xsi has three equal horiztonal bars; omicron is only slightly smaller than the other letters; pi has extended horizontal; rho has small rounded closed eye; sigma has horizontal top and bottom, with slihgtly variable mid-strokes; phi has small oval eye, with vertical often extended; omega is notably variable, always closed, but ranging from tear-drop to full circle on or even above and detached from the base line.",[54,60,67],{"type":55,"l":56,"from":57,"to":57,"h":58,"unit":59,"atLeast":58,"atMost":58},"letterHeight","Line 1","line1","18","mm",{"type":55,"l":61,"from":62,"to":63,"h":64,"unit":59,"atLeast":65,"atMost":66},"Line 2-23","line2","